          "date": "2019-03-11 07:07:51.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-6656 qmt: Fix non-atomic allocation under lock",
        "message": "LU-6656 qmt: Fix non-atomic allocation under lock\n\nIn qmt_glimpse_lock:\nWhile the resource lock (a spin lock) is held, it does\n\nOBD_ALLOC_PTR(work);\n\nThis allocation is not atomic, so it can potentially sleep.\nSleeping with a spinlock held is not a good idea in\ngeneral, and (per Andreas) it is specifically not allowed\nfor GFP_NOFS allocations.\n\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <paf@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I4ed2cd5e127bb2aa47235416ff1f97b9ac7826bc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
